      • getFps

        public int getFps()
        Get the frame rate.

        It is set to the fps value returned in the corresponding itag in the YouTube player response.

        It defaults to the standard value associated with this itag.

        Note that this value is only known for video itags, so FPS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN is returned for non video itags.

        Returns:
        the frame rate or FPS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN

      • setFps

        public void setFps​(int fps)
        Set the frame rate.

        It is only known for video itags, so FPS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN is set/used for non video itags or if the sample rate value is less than or equal to 0.

        Parameters:
        fps - the frame rate

      • getAverageBitrate

        public int getAverageBitrate()
        Get the average bitrate.

        It is only known for audio itags, so AVERAGE_BITRATE_UNKNOWN is always returned for other itag types.

        Bitrate of video itags and precise bitrate of audio itags can be known using getBitrate().

        Returns:
        the average bitrate or AVERAGE_BITRATE_UNKNOWN
        See Also:
        getBitrate()

      • getSampleRate

        public int getSampleRate()
        Get the sample rate.

        It is only known for audio itags, so SAMPLE_RATE_UNKNOWN is returned for non audio itags, or if the sample rate is unknown.

        Returns:
        the sample rate or SAMPLE_RATE_UNKNOWN

      • setSampleRate

        public void setSampleRate​(int sampleRate)
        Set the sample rate.

        It is only known for audio itags, so SAMPLE_RATE_UNKNOWN is set/used for non audio itags, or if the sample rate value is less than or equal to 0.

        Parameters:
        sampleRate - the sample rate of an audio itag

      • getAudioChannels

        public int getAudioChannels()
        Get the number of audio channels.

        It is only known for audio itags, so AUDIO_CHANNELS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN is returned for non audio itags, or if it is unknown.

        Returns:
        the number of audio channels or AUDIO_CHANNELS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN

        public void setAudioChannels​(int audioChannels)
        Set the number of audio channels.

        It is only known for audio itags, so AUDIO_CHANNELS_NOT_APPLICABLE_OR_UNKNOWN is set/used for non audio itags, or if the audioChannels value is less than or equal to 0.

        Parameters:
        audioChannels - the number of audio channels of an audio itag

      • getTargetDurationSec

        public int getTargetDurationSec()
        Get the targetDurationSec value.

        This value is the average time in seconds of the duration of sequences of livestreams and ended livestreams. It is only returned by YouTube for these stream types, and makes no sense for videos, so TARGET_DURATION_SEC_UNKNOWN is returned for those.

        Returns:
        the targetDurationSec value or TARGET_DURATION_SEC_UNKNOWN

      • setTargetDurationSec

        public void setTargetDurationSec​(int targetDurationSec)
        Set the targetDurationSec value.

        This value is the average time in seconds of the duration of sequences of livestreams and ended livestreams.

        It is only returned for these stream types by YouTube and makes no sense for videos, so TARGET_DURATION_SEC_UNKNOWN will be set/used for video streams or if this value is less than or equal to 0.

        Parameters:
        targetDurationSec - the target duration of a segment of streams which are using the live delivery method type

      • getApproxDurationMs

        public long getApproxDurationMs()
        Get the approxDurationMs value.

        It is only known for DASH progressive streams, so APPROX_DURATION_MS_UNKNOWN is returned for other stream types or if this value is less than or equal to 0.

        Returns:
        the approxDurationMs value or APPROX_DURATION_MS_UNKNOWN

      • setApproxDurationMs

        public void setApproxDurationMs​(long approxDurationMs)
        Set the approxDurationMs value.

        It is only known for DASH progressive streams, so APPROX_DURATION_MS_UNKNOWN is set/used for other stream types or if this value is less than or equal to 0.

        Parameters:
        approxDurationMs - the approximate duration of a DASH progressive stream, in milliseconds

      • getContentLength
